gobblin.azkaban

Class AzkabanJobLauncher

  • java.lang.Object
    • azkaban.jobExecutor.AbstractJob
      • gobblin.azkaban.AzkabanJobLauncher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    azkaban.jobExecutor.Job, ApplicationLauncher, JobLauncher, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class AzkabanJobLauncher
extends azkaban.jobExecutor.AbstractJob
implements ApplicationLauncher, JobLauncher
    A utility class for launching a Gobblin Hadoop MR job through Azkaban.

    By default, this class will use the MRJobLauncher to launch and run the Gobblin job unless a different job launcher type is explicitly specified in the job configuration using ConfigurationKeys.JOB_LAUNCHER_TYPE_KEY.

    If the Azkaban job type is not contained in JOB_TYPES_WITH_AUTOMATIC_TOKEN, the launcher assumes that the job does not get authentication tokens from Azkaban and it will negotiate them itself. See TokenUtils.getHadoopTokens(gobblin.configuration.State) for more information.
